 nomination==\n===Candidates===\n====Declared====\n*Robert Barb<ref name=\"3PMTgov\"/>\n**Running mate: Joshua Thomas\n\n==General election==\n===Predictions===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Source\n!Ranking\n!As of\n|-\n|[[The Cook Political Report]]<ref>{{cite web | title=2019-2020 Gubernatorial race ratings | url=https://cookpolitical.com/ratings/governor-race-ratings| website=The Cook Political Report | accessdate=November 30, 2018}}</ref>\n| {{sort|100|Tossup}}\n| April 3, 2020\n|-\n|[[Inside Elections]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insideelections.com/ratings/spectrum/2019-20-gubernatorial-ratings-february-1-2019/gubernatorial|title=Gubernatorial Ratings|website=Inside Elections|accessdate=February 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| {{sort|100|Tossup}} \n| April 23, 2020\n|-\n|[[Sabato's Crystal Ball]]<ref>{{cite web | title=Our Final 2016 picks | url=http://crystalball.centerforpolitics.org/crystalball/2020-governor/ | website=Sabato's Crystal Ball | accessdate=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n| {{sort|100|Tossup}}\n| January 16, 2020\n|-\n|[[Politico]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/2020-election/race-forecasts-and-predictions/governor/|title=We rated every gubernatorial race in 2020. Here's who we think will win.|website= Poltico|access-date= November 19, 2019}}</ref>\n| style=\"background:#fcc\"|{{sort|098|Lean R}}\n|April 19, 2020\n|}\n\n===Polling===\n{{collapse top|1=<span style=\"font-size:88%;\">Hypothetical polling</span>|left=yes|bg=#B0CEFF;line-height:135%;|border=none}}\n;with Ron Vandevender\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;text-align:center;\"\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size{{efn|name=key}}\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:50px;\"| Mike<br>Cooney (D)\n! style=\"width:50px;\"| Tim<br>Fox (R)\n! style=\"width:50px;\"| Greg<br>Gianforte (R)\n! style=\"width:50px;\"| Albert<br>Olszewski (R)\n! style=\"width:50px;\"| Ron<br>Vandevender (L)\n! style=\"width:50px;\"| Whitn