{"title_page": "Watchlist of the Rare Breeds Survival Trust", "text_new": "The '''Watch list of the Rare Breeds Survival Trust''' is a listing of rare and native United Kingdom [[breed]]s of domestic cattle, sheep, pigs, horses, goats and [[poultry]], compiled by the [[Rare Breeds Survival Trust]].<ref name=watch>[http://www.rbst.org.uk/Our-Work/Watchlist/Watchlist2 Rare Breeds Survival Trust watch list] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151118063241/http://www.rbst.org.uk/Our-Work/Watchlist/Watchlist2 |date=2015-11-18 }} accessed June 2016</ref> \n\n[[Mammal]]ian farm breeds are classified into five levels of endangerment, based on the number of breeding females. The five classes are:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n!    !!  style=\"width: 200px\"  | Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"; style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  | Cattle\n|   under 150   ||     style=\"width: 200px\" |   150\u2013250      ||    style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\"  | 250\u2013450   ||     style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\"  | 450\u2013750  ||    style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\"  |750\u20131500\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"; style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  |  Goats\n|  under 100  ||   100\u2013200   ||   200\u2013300   || 300\u2013500  ||   500\u20131000\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"; style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  |  Horses\n|   under 300 ||  300\u2013500    ||  500\u2013900    ||  900\u20131500 ||   1500\u20133000\n|-\n! style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  |  Pigs\n|  under 100  ||   100\u2013200   ||   200\u2013300   || 300\u2013500  ||   500\u20131000\n|-\n! style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  |Sheep\n|   under 300 ||  300\u2013500    ||  500\u2013900    ||  900\u20131500 ||   1500\u20133000\n|-\n|}\nPoultry \u2013 chickens, ducks, geese and turkeys \u2013 are not categorised by degree of numerical rarity; some are classified as \"priority breeds\".<ref name=rbst-2013-watchlist>{{cite web|title=RBST watchlist 2013|url=https://www.rbst.org.uk/watchlist.pdf|website=Rare Breeds Survival Trust|publisher=Rare Breeds Survival Trust|accessdate=17 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715025957/https://www.rbst.org.uk/watchlist.pdf|archive-date=15 July 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=rbst-pountry-2014>{{cite web|title=Poultry Breeds at Risk|url=https://www.rbst.org.uk/poultry-breeds-at-risk-2014.pdf|website=Rare Breeds Survival Trust|publisher=Rare Breeds Survival Trust|accessdate=17 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701233204/https://www.rbst.org.uk/poultry-breeds-at-risk-2014.pdf|archive-date=1 July 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n== Listed breeds ==\n\n===Cattle===\n\nIn 2017, the watch-listed cattle breeds were:{{r|rbst2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n|   style=\"width: 200px;\" |  The [[Chillingham Wild Cattle]]   ||     style=\"width: 200px;\" |   Native [[Aberdeen Angus]]      ||    style=\"width: 200px;\" |  {{nobreak|[[Lincoln Red]] (original population)}}   ||     style=\"width: 200px\" | [[Gloucester cattle|Gloucester]]  ||    style=\"width: 200px\" | [[British White]]\n|-\n|   {{nobreak|[[Dairy Shorthorn]] (original population)}}   ||    [[Whitebred Shorthorn]]     ||      ||  [[Shetland cattle|Shetland]]   ||  [[Irish Moiled]]\n|-\n|   Northern Dairy Shorthorn   ||         ||      ||     ||  Traditional [[Hereford (cattle)|Hereford]]\n|-\n|   [[Vaynol cattle|Vaynol]]   ||         ||      ||     ||   [[White Park cattle|White Park]]\n|-\n|}\nThe other native breeds listed were the Aberdeen Angus, [[Ayrshire cattle|Ayrshire]], [[Beef Shorthorn]], [[Belted Galloway]], [[North Devon cattle|Devon]], [[Galloway cattle|Galloway]], [[Guernsey cattle|Guernsey]], [[Hereford (cattle)|Hereford]], [[Highland cattle|Highland]], [[Jersey cattle|Jersey]], Lincoln Red, [[English Longhorn|Longhorn]], [[Luing cattle|Luing]], [[Red Poll]], [[Beef Shorthorn|Shorthorn]], [[South Devon cattle|South Devon]], [[Sussex cattle|Sussex]] and [[Welsh Black cattle|Welsh Black]]. The Irish [[Kerry (cattle)|Kerry]] breed was also considered part of the agricultural heritage of the United Kingdom.{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n===Sheep===\n\nSheep breeds listed in 2017 were:{{r|rbst2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n|   style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |  \u2014  ||     style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |   \u2014   ||    style=\"width: 200px;\" |   [[Boreray (sheep)|Boreray]]  ||     style=\"width: 200px\" |  [[Border Leicester]] ||    style=\"width: 200px\" |   [[Balwen Welsh Mountain (sheep)|Balwen Welsh Mountain]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||   [[Devon and Cornwall Longwool]]   ||   [[Castlemilk Moorit (sheep)|Castlemilk Moorit]]   || [[Devon Closewool]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||  [[English Leicester (sheep)|Leicester Longwool]]    ||  [[Cotswold sheep|Cotswold]]    ||    [[Dorset Down]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||  [[Lincoln (sheep)|Lincoln Longwool]]    ||    [[Derbyshire Gritstone]]  ||    [[Greyface Dartmoor]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||   [[North Ronaldsay sheep|North Ronaldsay]]   ||   [[Dorset (sheep)|Dorset Horn]]   ||    [[Llanwenog (sheep)|Llanwenog]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||   [[Whitefaced Woodland]]   ||   [[Hill Radnor]]   ||    [[Norfolk Horn]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||   [[Manx Loaghtan]]   ||     [[Oxford Down]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||   [[Portland (sheep)|Portland]]   ||   [[Whiteface Dartmoor]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||   [[Soay sheep|Soay]]   ||\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||   [[Teeswater (sheep)|Teeswater]]   ||\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||    [[Wensleydale (sheep)|Wensleydale]]  ||\n|-\n|}\n\nThe other native breeds listed were the [[Badger Face Welsh Mountain (sheep)|Badger Face Welsh Mountain]], [[Beulah Speckled Face]], [[Black Welsh Mountain]], [[Scottish Blackface]], [[Bluefaced Leicester]], [[Brecknock Hill Cheviot]], [[Clun Forest sheep|Clun Forest]], [[Dalesbred]], [[Exmoor Horn]], [[Hampshire sheep|Hampshire Down]], [[Hebridean (sheep)|Hebridean]], [[Herdwick]], [[Jacob (sheep)|Jacob]], [[Kerry Hill (sheep)|Kerry Hill]], [[Llandovery Whiteface Hill]], [[Lleyn sheep|Lleyn]], [[Lonk]], [[North Country Cheviot]], [[Romney (sheep)|Romney]], [[Rough Fell]], [[Ryeland]], [[Shetland sheep|Shetland]], [[Shropshire (sheep)|Shropshire]], [[Southdown (sheep)|Southdown]], South Country [[Cheviot sheep|Cheviot]], [[South Wales Mountain]], [[Suffolk sheep|Suffolk]], [[Swaledale]], [[Welsh Hill Speckled]], [[Welsh Mountain sheep|Welsh Mountain]] and [[Wiltshire Horn]]. The Irish [[Galway (sheep)|Galway]] breed was also listed.{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n===Pigs===\n\nThe pig breeds listed in 2017 were:{{r|rbst2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n|   style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |  \u2014    ||     style=\"width: 200px;\" |   [[British Landrace]]   ||    style=\"width: 200px;\" |  [[Berkshire (pig)|Berkshire]]  ||     style=\"width: 200px\" |  [[British Saddleback]] ||   style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |  \u2014   \n|-\n|      ||   [[British Lop]]      ||  [[Large White (pig)|Large White]]   ||    [[Gloucestershire Old Spots]] ||\n|-\n|      ||     [[Large Black (pig)|Large Black]]     ||  [[Tamworth (pig)|Tamworth]]     ||   [[Oxford Sandy and Black]]  ||\n|-\n|      ||    [[Middle White]]        ||      ||   [[Welsh (pig)|Welsh]]    ||\n|-\n|}\n\n===Goats===\nIn 2017 the [[Bagot goat|Bagot]] was listed as \"endangered\" and the [[Golden Guernsey]] as \"minority\".{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n===Horses and ponies===\n\nThe listed horse breeds in 2017 were:{{r|rbst2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n|   style=\"width: 200px;\" |  [[Cleveland Bay]]  ||     style=\"width: 200px;\" |   [[Dartmoor Pony]]    ||    style=\"width: 200px;\" |  [[Clydesdale (horse)|Clydesdale]]  ||     style=\"width: 200px\" | [[New Forest Pony]]||   style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |  \u2014   \n|-\n|    [[Dales Pony]]  ||    [[Exmoor Pony]]      ||  [[Fell Pony]]     ||    [[Shire Horse]] ||\n|-\n|    [[Eriskay Pony]]    ||         ||    [[Highland Pony]]  ||     ||\n|-\n|    [[Hackney horse|Hackney Horse and Pony]]  ||         ||      ||     ||\n|-\n|    [[Suffolk Punch]]  ||         ||      ||     ||\n|-\n|}\n\nThe other native breeds listed were the [[Shetland pony|Shetland]] and the [[Welsh Pony and Cob]], and the [[Irish Draught]] and [[Connemara pony|Connemara]] breeds of Ireland were also included.{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n=== Poultry ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!  !! Chickens !! Ducks !! Geese  !! Turkeys\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"; style=\"width: 200px; text-align: left\"  | Priority breeds\n|    style=\"width: 200px;\" |  [[Andalusian chicken|Andalusian]]<br>[[Brussbar]]<br>[[Burmese chicken|Burmese]]<br>[[Campine (chicken)|Campine]]<br>[[Derbyshire Redcap]]<br>[[Dorking chicken|Dorking]]<br>[[Hamburg chicken|Hamburg]]<br>[[Malay chicken|Malay]]<br>[[Marsh Daisy chicken|Marsh Daisy]]<br>[[Modern Game fowl|Modern Game]]<br>[[Modern Langshan]]<br>[[North Holland Blue]]<br>[[Old English Pheasant Fowl]]<br>[[Rhodebar]]<br>[[Manx Rumpy|Rumpless Game]]<br>[[Scots Dumpy]]<br>[[Scots Grey]]<br>[[Sicilian Buttercup chicken|Sicilian Buttercup]]<br>[[White-faced Black Spanish chicken|Spanish]]<br>[[Sultan chicken|Sultan]]<br>[[Sussex chicken|Sussex]]<br>[[Welbar]]   ||     style=\"width: 200px;\" |   [[Orpington (duck)|Orpington]]<br>[[Shetland (duck)|Shetland]]<br>[[Silver Bantam (duck)|Silver Bantam]]<br>[[Stanbridge White (duck)|Stanbridge White]]<br>[[Welsh Harlequin]]<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>   ||    style=\"width: 200px;\" |  [[Brecon Buff (goose)|Brecon Buff]]<br>[[Buff Back (goose)|Buff Back]]<br>[[Embden (goose)|Embden]] (UK type)<br>[[Grey Back (goose)|Grey Back]]<br>[[Pilgrim (goose)|Pilgrim]]<br>[[Sebastopol (goose)|Sebastopol]]<br>[[Shetland (goose)|Shetland]]<br>[[Toulouse (goose)|Toulouse]] (exhibition)<br>[[West of England (goose)|West of England]]<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>   ||     style=\"width: 200px\" |     [[Blue (turkey)|Blue]]<br>[[Bourbon Red]]<br>[[British White (turkey)|British White]]<br>[[Bronze (turkey)|Bronze]]<br>[[Buff (turkey)|Buff]]<br>[[Cr\u00f6llwitzer (turkey)|Cr\u00f6llwitzer]]<br>[[Harvey Speckled]]<br>[[Narragansett (turkey)|Narragansett]]<br>[[Nebraskan (turkey)|Nebraskan]]<br>[[Norfolk Black]]<br>[[Slate (turkey)|Slate]]<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"; style=\"width: 200px; text-align: left\"  |  Other breeds\n|    [[Ancona chicken|Ancona]]<br>[[Australorp]]<br>British [[Araucana]]<br>British [[Faverolles chicken|Faverolles]]<br>Buff [[Orpington chicken|Orpington]]<br>[[Cochin chicken|Cochin]]<br>[[Cream Legbar]]<br>[[Croad Langshan]]<br>[[Cornish chicken|Indian Game]]<br>[[Ixworth chicken|Ixworth]]<br>[[Legbar]]<br>[[Leghorn chicken|Leghorn]]<br>[[Minorca chicken|Minorca]]<br>[[Nankin chicken|Nankin]]<br>[[Norfolk Grey]]<br>[[Old English Game]]<br>[[Orpington chicken|Orpington]] (non-Buff)<br>[[Rosecomb]]<br>[[Sebright chicken|Sebright]]    ||   [[Abacot Ranger]]<br>[[Aylesbury (duck)|Aylesbury]]<br>[[Black East Indian (duck)|Black East Indian]]<br>[[Campbell (duck)|Campbell]]<br>[[Cayuga (duck)|Cayuga]]<br>[[Crested (duck breed)|Crested]]<br>[[Magpie (duck)|Magpie]]<br>[[Rouen (duck)|Rouen]] (exhibition)<br>[[Silver Appleyard]]<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>    ||      ||    \n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|45em|refs=\n\n<ref name=rbst2017>[https://web.archive.org/web/20170806021906/https://www.rbst.org.uk/content/download/4571/65927/version/1/file/Watchlist+2017+A3+pg+1+-+FINAL+VERSION.pdf Watchlist 2017\u20132018]. Rare Breeds Survival Trust. Archived 6 August 2017.</ref>\n\n\n}}\n\n[[Category:Rare breed conservation]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Watch list of the Rare Breeds Survival Trust''' is a listing of rare and native United Kingdom [[breed]]s of domestic cattle, sheep, pigs, horses, goats and [[poultry]], compiled by the [[Rare Breeds Survival Trust]].<ref name=watch>[http://www.rbst.org.uk/Our-Work/Watchlist/Watchlist2 Rare Breeds Survival Trust watch list] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151118063241/http://www.rbst.org.uk/Our-Work/Watchlist/Watchlist2 |date=2015-11-18 }} accessed June 2016</ref> \n\n[[Mammal]]ian farm breeds are classified into five levels of endangerment, based on the number of breeding females. The five classes are:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n!    !!  style=\"width: 200px\"  | Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"; style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  | Cattle\n|   under 150   ||     style=\"width: 200px\" |   150\u2013250      ||    style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\"  | 250\u2013450   ||     style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\"  | 450\u2013750  ||    style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\"  |750\u20131500\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"; style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  |  Goats\n|  under 100  ||   100\u2013200   ||   200\u2013300   || 300\u2013500  ||   500\u20131000\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"; style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  |  Horses\n|   under 300 ||  300\u2013500    ||  500\u2013900    ||  900\u20131500 ||   1500\u20133000\n|-\n! style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  |  Pigs\n|  under 100  ||   100\u2013200   ||   200\u2013300   || 300\u2013500  ||   500\u20131000\n|-\n! style=\"width: 120px; text-align: left\"  |Sheep\n|   under 300 ||  300\u2013500    ||  500\u2013900    ||  900\u20131500 ||   1500\u20133000\n|-\n|}\nPoultry \u2013 chickens, ducks, geese and turkeys \u2013 are not categorised by degree of numerical rarity; some are classified as \"priority breeds\".<ref name=rbst-2013-watchlist>{{cite web|title=RBST watchlist 2013|url=https://www.rbst.org.uk/watchlist.pdf|website=Rare Breeds Survival Trust|publisher=Rare Breeds Survival Trust|accessdate=17 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715025957/https://www.rbst.org.uk/watchlist.pdf|archive-date=15 July 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=rbst-pountry-2014>{{cite web|title=Poultry Breeds at Risk|url=https://www.rbst.org.uk/poultry-breeds-at-risk-2014.pdf|website=Rare Breeds Survival Trust|publisher=Rare Breeds Survival Trust|accessdate=17 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701233204/https://www.rbst.org.uk/poultry-breeds-at-risk-2014.pdf|archive-date=1 July 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n== Listed breeds ==\n\n===Cattle===\n\nIn 2017, the watch-listed cattle breeds were:{{r|rbst2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n|   style=\"width: 200px;\" |  The [[Chillingham Wild Cattle]]   ||     style=\"width: 200px;\" |   Native [[Aberdeen Angus]]      ||    style=\"width: 200px;\" |  {{nobreak|[[Lincoln Red]] (original population)}}   ||     style=\"width: 200px\" | [[Gloucester cattle|Gloucester]]  ||    style=\"width: 200px\" | [[British White]]\n|-\n|   {{nobreak|[[Dairy Shorthorn]] (original population)}}   ||    [[Whitebred Shorthorn]]     ||      ||  [[Shetland cattle|Shetland]]   ||  [[Irish Moiled]]\n|-\n|   Northern Dairy Shorthorn   ||         ||      ||     ||  Traditional [[Hereford (cattle)|Hereford]]\n|-\n|   [[Vaynol cattle|Vaynol]]   ||         ||      ||     ||   [[White Park cattle|White Park]]\n|-\n|}\nThe other native breeds listed were the Aberdeen Angus, [[Ayrshire cattle|Ayrshire]], [[Beef Shorthorn]], [[Belted Galloway]], [[North Devon cattle|Devon]], [[Galloway cattle|Galloway]], [[Guernsey cattle|Guernsey]], [[Hereford (cattle)|Hereford]], [[Highland cattle|Highland]], [[Jersey cattle|Jersey]], Lincoln Red, [[English Longhorn|Longhorn]], [[Luing cattle|Luing]], [[Red Poll]], [[Beef Shorthorn|Shorthorn]], [[South Devon cattle|South Devon]], [[Sussex cattle|Sussex]] and [[Welsh Black cattle|Welsh Black]]. The Irish [[Kerry (cattle)|Kerry]] breed was also considered part of the agricultural heritage of the United Kingdom.{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n===Sheep===\n\nSheep breeds listed in 2017 were:{{r|rbst2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n|   style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |  \u2014  ||     style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |   \u2014   ||    style=\"width: 200px;\" |   [[Boreray (sheep)|Boreray]]  ||     style=\"width: 200px\" |  [[Border Leicester]] ||    style=\"width: 200px\" |   [[Balwen Welsh Mountain (sheep)|Balwen Welsh Mountain]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||   [[Devon and Cornwall Longwool]]   ||   [[Castlemilk Moorit (sheep)|Castlemilk Moorit]]   || [[Devon Closewool]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||  [[English Leicester (sheep)|Leicester Longwool]]    ||  [[Cotswold sheep|Cotswold]]    ||    [[Dorset Down]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||  [[Lincoln (sheep)|Lincoln Longwool]]    ||    [[Derbyshire Gritstone]]  ||    [[Greyface Dartmoor]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||   [[North Ronaldsay sheep|North Ronaldsay]]   ||   [[Dorset (sheep)|Dorset Horn]]   ||    [[Llanwenog (sheep)|Llanwenog]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||   [[Whitefaced Woodland]]   ||   [[Hill Radnor]]   ||    [[Norfolk Horn]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||   [[Manx Loaghtan]]   ||     [[Oxford Down]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||   [[Portland (sheep)|Portland]]   ||   [[Whiteface Dartmoor]]\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||   [[Soay sheep|Soay]]   ||\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||   [[Teeswater (sheep)|Teeswater]]   ||\n|-\n|      ||         ||      ||    [[Wensleydale (sheep)|Wensleydale]]  ||\n|-\n|}\n\nThe other native breeds listed were the [[Badger Face Welsh Mountain (sheep)|Badger Face Welsh Mountain]], [[Beulah Speckled Face]], [[Black Welsh Mountain]], [[Scottish Blackface]], [[Bluefaced Leicester]], [[Brecknock Hill Cheviot]], [[Clun Forest sheep|Clun Forest]], [[Dalesbred]], [[Exmoor Horn]], [[Hampshire sheep|Hampshire Down]], [[Hebridean (sheep)|Hebridean]], [[Herdwick]], [[Jacob (sheep)|Jacob]], [[Kerry Hill (sheep)|Kerry Hill]], [[Llandovery Whiteface Hill]], [[Lleyn sheep|Lleyn]], [[Lonk]], [[North Country Cheviot]], [[Romney (sheep)|Romney]], [[Rough Fell]], [[Ryeland]], [[Shetland sheep|Shetland]], [[Shropshire (sheep)|Shropshire]], [[Southdown (sheep)|Southdown]], South Country [[Cheviot sheep|Cheviot]], [[South Wales Mountain]], [[Suffolk sheep|Suffolk]], [[Swaledale]], [[Welsh Hill Speckled]], [[Welsh Mountain sheep|Welsh Mountain]] and [[Wiltshire Horn]]. The Irish [[Galway (sheep)|Galway]] breed was also listed.{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n===Pigs===\n\nThe pig breeds listed in 2017 were:{{r|rbst2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n|   style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |  \u2014    ||     style=\"width: 200px;\" |   [[British Landrace]]   ||    style=\"width: 200px;\" |  [[Berkshire (pig)|Berkshire]]  ||     style=\"width: 200px\" |  [[British Saddleback]] ||   style=\"width: 200px; text-align: center\" |  \u2014   \n|-\n|      ||   [[British Lop]]      ||  [[Large White (pig)|Large White]]   ||    [[Gloucestershire Old Spots]] ||\n|-\n|      ||     [[Large Black (pig)|Large Black]]     ||  [[Tamworth (pig)|Tamworth]]     ||   [[Oxford Sandy and Black]]  ||\n|-\n|      ||    [[Middle White]]        ||      ||   [[Welsh (pig)|Welsh]]    ||\n|-\n|}\n\n===Goats===\nIn 2017 the [[Bagot goat|Bagot]] was listed as \"endangered\" and the [[Golden Guernsey]] as \"minority\".{{r|rbst2017}}\n\n===Horses and ponies===\n\nThe listed horse breeds in 2017 were:{{r|rbst2017}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Critical !! Endangered !! Vulnerable !! At risk  !! Minority \n|-\n|   style=\"width: 200px;\" |  [[Cleveland Bay]]  ||     style=